PC-BASIC 3.23
REFERENCE



ABS

ABS(x) function
---------------
Returns the absolute value of x. x is an expression with a numeric value.
If x has a string value, ABS raises a TYPE MISMATCH error.


ASC

ASC(x) function
---------------
Returns the ASCII code for the first character of x. x is an expression with a string value.
If x has a numeric value, ASC raises TYPE MISMATCH.
IF x="", ASC raises ILLEGAL FUNCTION CALL.




